      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "@gmaxwell Just to get this clear, when I use -tor this is for reaching Tor addresses (hidden services) and this patch would disable listening, if not explicitly enabled and would also lead to disable -upnp and -discover (if not explicitly enabled). How does this break hidden services?\n\n@sipa I guess the patch should be changed to do this for -onlynet=Tor then?\n",
